As someone who usually assumed that hentai meant badly plotted anime, I was astonished to recently run across a hentai that actually works, in fact is downright hilarious, as a story: Women at Work (2005), originally titled The Guts! and apparently based on a video game.

Akiyoshis life fell apart for him when he got turned down by the girl of his dreams because his slight build makes him look like a wimp, but in response he gets a flash of inspiration.  Instead of paying money to join a health club in order to build up his muscles, he will go to work in the construction industry and get paid to build up his muscles!  Unfortunately (fortunately?), he has picked a really peculiar company to work for.  What follows are Akiyoshi surviving several brilliantly conceived situations as very different women, with very different personalities and very different needs, all decide to go for him.  From the boss lady with unusual ideas for employment testing, to the secretary with unusual ideas for monitoring the health of his diet, to the neighbor with unusual ideas for compensation for the sleep reducing noise of nearby construction, to the muscular forewoman with unusual ideas for motivating him, to the newbie girl hiding out as a boy worker with unusual ideas for thanking him for keeping her secret, to the rich girl worker with unusual ideas for ordering him around, Akiyoshi has never been in better shape or more exhausted!

The animation is competently (and explicitly) done, as is both the English voice acting and the English subtitling of the Japanese voice acted version of this 2 episode OVA.  Its even got a rousing, if somewhat confusing, motivational spiel by the forewoman at the end, depending on what she meant by it, which even she isn't sure of.  Actually recommended.
